  "text": "A) Scatter plot of total PDE activity and PDE3 activity measured in COCs for each of five experiments. B) The level of total PDE activity was determined in both COC and DO. PDE activity was measured in the presence of three different inhibitors, 1 mM 3-isobutyl-1-methyxanthine (IBMX, nonspecific), 10 M cilostamide (PDE3-specific), and 10 M rolipram (PDE4-specific). C) The specific PDE3 (cilostamide-sensitive) and PDE4 (rolipram-sensitive) activity was calculated by subtracting the activity measured in the pres- ulated (P Ͻ 0.05) by the hCG treatment (Fig. 6 ). In our experimental conditions, the oocytes did not resume meiosis within the time frame of 2 h (data not shown). Previous studies have also shown that the stimulation of meiosis by hCG/LH results in resumption of meiosis by 50% of the oocytes after 3 h and 90% after 4 h [CITATION_1] .",
